# Stock — environment (spec §14.2: API key handling). Copy to `.env`.
#
# Two ways to enable Claude:
#
# 1) NATIVE (iOS/Android): the app talks to Anthropic directly via the SDK and
#    needs the key in the client. EXPO_PUBLIC_* is inlined into the bundle —
#    fine for a personal install, must NOT ship in a distributed binary.
EXPO_PUBLIC_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
#
# 2) WEB (Pages / serve:web): the key must NOT be in the browser bundle, so the
#    web build calls the Supabase `claude` Edge Function instead. Set the
#    deployed function URL here (the Anthropic key lives in Supabase secrets,
#    never in the client). Leave (1) blank for web.
EXPO_PUBLIC_CLAUDE_PROXY_URL=
# Optional: must match STOCK_PROXY_SECRET set on the function. On a public
# Pages deploy this still ships in the bundle — it's throttling/obscurity, not
# real auth. The real protection is the key staying server-side; set an
# Anthropic spend limit as the backstop.
EXPO_PUBLIC_CLAUDE_PROXY_SECRET=
#
# 3) AUTH + CROSS-DEVICE SYNC (web): magic-link sign-in via Supabase Auth,
#    per-user data in Postgres with RLS. Same Supabase project as the proxy.
#    The anon key is publishable (safe in the client) — RLS does the gating.
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://xsmnfcmtbpeaccnyinkr.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
